{"lemma":"حَنانٌ","slug":"حَنانٌ","root":"ح.ن.ن","root_slug":"ح-ن-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ن-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَنان","root":"حنن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9243","n9249","n9250"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَنَّ (ḥanna) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mercy, kindness, affection","examples":[{"text":"يَا يَحْيَى خُذِ الْكِتَابَ بِقُوَّةٍ ۖ وَآتَيْنَاهُ الْحُكْمَ صَبِيًّا / وَحَنَانًا مِّن لَدُنَّا وَزَكَاةً ۖ وَكَانَ تَقِيًّا"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tenderness","examples":[{"text":"حَنانُكَ يُشَبِّهُ لَمْسَةَ الرِيَاحِ اللَطِيفَةِ فِي لَيْلَةٍ صَيْفِيَّةٍ هَادِئَةٍ.","english":"Your tenderness is like a gentle breeze on a quiet summer night."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"compassion"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ħa.naːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9243","headword_ar":"حَنَانٌ","root":"Hn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mercy, compassion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tenderness of heart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) which is the same; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hin~apN","text_ar":"حِنَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr; (Kr, TA;) for which the vulgar say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Han~iy~ipN","text_ar":"حَنِّيِّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Han~apN","text_ar":"حَنَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in like manner] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compassion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHanaAnFA mino ladun~aA","text_ar":"وَحَنَانًا مِنْ لَدُنَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xix. 14], respecting which I 'Ab is related by 'Ikrimeh to have said, I know not what is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHanaAnu","text_ar":"الحَنَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And mercy from us."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) The Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HanaAnaka yaA rab~i","text_ar":"حَنَانَكَ يَا رَبِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HanaAnayoka","text_ar":"حَنَانَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[I beg"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy mercy, O my Lord"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: both signify the same; i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHomataka","text_ar":"رَحْمَتَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) the latter is the expression commonly used: (A 'Obeyd, in a marginal note in a copy of the S:) or [rather] the latter means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have mercy on me time after time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with mercy after mercy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) it is a dualized inf. n., of which the verb is not expressed; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lab~ayoka","text_ar":"لَبَّيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEodayoka","text_ar":"سَعْدَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or it means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"let thy mercy be continuous to me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whenever I receive mercy and good from Thee, let it not cease, but be conjoined with other mercy from Thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, TA:) the dual form is not to be understood as restricting the signification to duality: (Suh, TA:) the word is not used in this form otherwise than as a prefixed noun: (Sb, TA:) but sometimes they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HanFAnFA","text_ar":"حَنًانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the sing., without prefixing it. (ISd, TA.) They said also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHaAna A@ll~`hi waHanaAnayohi","text_ar":"سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهِ وَحَنَانَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I extol,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"celebrate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declare, the absolute purity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glory, of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and I beg his mercy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as they said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHaAna A@ll~`hi warayoHaAnahu","text_ar":"سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهِ وَرَيْحَانَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HanaAna A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"حَنَانَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaA*a A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"مَعَاذَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I seek the protection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preservation, of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rizoqN","text_ar":"رِزْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Means of subsistence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barakapN","text_ar":"بَرَكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a blessing; any good that is bestowed by God; prosperity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good fortune; increase;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A quality inspiring reverence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veneration"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Umawee, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gravity, staidness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sedateness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAtaraY","text_ar":"مَاتَرَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu HanaAnFA","text_ar":"لَهُ حَنَانًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou seest him not to possess any quality inspiring reverence"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (El-Umawee, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief, long continuing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","ISd","Suh","Sb"]},{"entry_id":"n9249","headword_ar":"حَنَّانٌ","root":"Hn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who yearns towards, longs for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desires, a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclines to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Han~aAnapN","text_ar":"حَنَّانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who remembers a former husband with yearning"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHnyn","text_ar":"الحنين"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and grieving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moaning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in tenderness for her children, when they are young, that the husband may maintain them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^an~aAnapN","text_ar":"اَنَّانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who yearns towards her former husband, and inclines to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who yearns towards her child,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"children, by her husband who has separated from her:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or a woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who yearns towards her former husband, and grieves for him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who marries, having been divorced, and yearns towards him who has divorced her."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 569.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) [because of the sound made by the twanging of its string;] accord. to AHn, as a proper name; but ISd holds it to be, when thus applied, an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant: (TA:) or a bow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twangs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"makes a sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when its string has been pulled and then let go."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwdN","text_ar":"عُودٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Han~aAnN","text_ar":"حَنَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lute that produces plaintive sounds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that excites lively emotions of sadness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of mirth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbN Han~aAnN","text_ar":"سَحَابٌ حَنَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clouds that have"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"produce"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haniyn","text_ar":"حَنِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moaning sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by their thunder heard from a distance,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haniyn","text_ar":"حَنِين"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sahomN Han~aAnN","text_ar":"سَهْمٌ حَنَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An arrow that produces a sound when thou triest its sonorific quality by turning it round between thy fingers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, K, TA: [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqarotuhu","text_ar":"نَقَرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naq~arotahu","text_ar":"نَقَّرْتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that produces a sound when it is turned round"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^udiyra","text_ar":"اُدِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^udir~a","text_ar":"اُدِرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the ends of the fingers upon the thumbs, by reason of the excellence and compactness of its wood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dar~a Als~ahomu","text_ar":"دَرَّ السَّهْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dr","text_ar":"در"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ximosN Han~aAnN","text_ar":"خِمْسٌ حَنَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAy^iSN","text_ar":"بَايِصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hurrying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard, journey in which the camels are watered only on the first and fifth days:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in the CK and a MS. copy of the K, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAbDN","text_ar":"نابضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] (K, TA) i. e. (As, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which there is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haniyn","text_ar":"حَنِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yearning"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the camels]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of its quickness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, K, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the camels yearn"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards their accustomed places"},{"kind":"text","text":"] ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHin~u","text_ar":"تَحِنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reason of fatigue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN Han~aAnN","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ حَنَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A conspicuous road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the old camel becomes joyous"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHin~u","text_ar":"يَحِنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanobasiTu","text_ar":"يَنْبَسِطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): or, accord. to the A,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road in which there is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heard"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haniyn","text_ar":"حَنِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yearning cry"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the camels;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN nah~aAmN","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ نَهَّامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning a road in which is [heard] a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahiym","text_ar":"نَهِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or chiding] of camels. (TA.) ―         -b2-  One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who shows favour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"presents a favourable aspect, to him who turns from him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shuns him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Merciful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having mercy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHan~aAnu","text_ar":"الحَنَّانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"a name of God; (K;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Merciful"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Is-hák, Az, IAth, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to his servants."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","As"]},{"entry_id":"n9250","headword_ar":"حِنَّانٌ","root":"Hn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hin~aA='N","text_ar":"حِنَّا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lawsonia inermis,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Egyptian privet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HnA^","text_ar":"حنا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K;) a dial. var. of the latter: (Fr, Th, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hun~aAnN","text_ar":"حُنَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be a pl.; (TA in the present art.;) i. e. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hin~aA='","text_ar":"حِنَّا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", anomalously; or a dial. var. thereof. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HnA^","text_ar":"حنا"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also what next follows.]"}],"source_refs":["Fr","Th","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AD%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86/","headword_ar":"حنان","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_15","lexicon_en":"Ibn Mālik, al-Alfāẓ al-Mukhtalifa fī l-Maʿānī al-Muʾtalifa (d. 1274 CE)","lexicon_ar":"الألفاظ المختلفة في المعاني المؤتلفة لابن مالك","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22475#3f0a46","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">بَاب الحنان والشفقة</span><br><br><span>رقتك ورحمتك ورأفتك وتحننك وإحسانك وإشفاقك وحدبك وحنوك وعطفك وترهيفك ورفرفتك ورفقك ومنك ولطفك وصفحك </span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_39","lexicon_en":"ʿAbdullāh ibn ʿAbbās, Gharīb al-Qurʾān fī Shiʿr al-ʿArab, also known as Masāʾil Nāfiʿ b. al-Azraq (d. 687 CE)","lexicon_ar":"غريب القرآن في شعر العرب لعبد الله بن عباس","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22475#649f4c","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">ح ن ن [حنانا]</span><br><span>قال: يا ابن عباس: أخبرني عن قول الله عز وجل: وَحَناناً مِنْ لَدُنَّا .</span><br><span>قال: رحمة من عندنا.</span><br><span>قال: وهل تعرف العرب ذلك؟</span><br><span>قال: نعم، أما سمعت طرفة بن العبد وهو يقول:</span><br><span>أبا منذر أفنيت فاستبق بعضنا </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> حنانيك بعض الشّرّ أهون من بعض </span>"}]}}